description: Number of isomorphism classes of posets with n points with property that there is no nonsingelton proper subset T for which x not in T implies x<T or x>T or x incomparable with every element of T.
references: J. A. Wright, There are 718 6-point topologies, quasi-orderings and transgraphs, Notices Amer. Math. Soc., 17 (1970), p. 646, Abstract #70T-A106.
links: J. A. Wright, Letter to N. J. A. Sloane, Apr 06 1972, listing 18 sequences

crossrefs: A subset of the posets enumerated in A003431. Cf. A046905.
